OmniProcessElement.PropertySetConfig:
{"controlWidth":12,"label":"TextBlock1","text":"

For Ministry Certificate:

  • Select Ministry Certificate template and proceed further.
  • Give a Document Name to Ministry Certificate and select the download type (i.e. word / PDF). By default, word is selected.
  • Attached File Format (defaulted to PDF), tells a PDF will be automatically attached in the related tab Files section of the case record on document generation.
  • Download the document.
  • Sign the certificate.
  • Go to files tab in the TPL app. Selected Signed Certificates library into the files.
  • Upload the signed certificate in that “Signed Certificates” library. (The library contains security to preserve signed documents from deletion).
  • Go to the related tabs of the selected case, in the files upload the document from signed certificate library.
  • Try to delete the newly signed certificate. The analyst will not have permission to delete the file.

  For Case History Template:

  • Select Case History template and proceed further.
  • Give a Document Name to Ministry Certificate and select the download type (i.e. word / PDF). By default, word is selected.
  • Attached File Format (defaulted to PDF), tells a PDF will be automatically attached in the related tab Files section of the case record on document generation.
  • Download the document.
